President Obama spoke with Governor Nathan Deal of Georgia, Governor Nikki Haley of South Carolina, Governor Pat McCrory of North Carolina, and Governor Rick Scott of Florida regarding preparations for Hurricane Matthew. The President assured them that the federal government would provide necessary resources to aid in their response efforts. He has already declared a state of emergency in Florida and ordered federal assistance to supplement local responses. The President emphasized the importance of residents following the guidance of emergency officials and taking the storm seriously. He encouraged those in the storm's potential path to stay updated through local media and assured that his team is actively preparing to respond to the hurricane.